====Usage notes====
* The adjective {{lang|zh|死}} ("dead, inactive, etc.") cannot be used as a [[predicative adjective]]. The sentence *{{lang|zh|這隻狗死}} generally does not mean "This dog is dead". For the meaning "is dead", usually the verb {{lang|zh|死}} in the perfect aspect ("to have died") is used instead:
*:{{zh-x|這 隻 狗 死 了。|This dog has '''died'''.}}
* The verb {{lang|zh|死}} ("to die") lacks a present meaning and denotes either past (in perfect aspect) or future (not in perfect aspect) events. It cannot be modified by the progressive aspect marker {{zh-l|正在}} or {{zh-l|著/着|tr=zhe}}.
*: {{zh-x|不死|"will not die", immortal}}
*: {{zh-x|沒 死|"did not die", alive}}

