{{wp|Death}}
{{IPAchar|/si/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɕi/}}

Appears to be a [[conflation]] of {{der|ja|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|死}}, with an {{inh|ja|ojp|-}} root that happened to have a similar pronunciation to the {{cog|ltc|-}} and was probably cognate with {{m|ja|去る|tr=saru||to [[go]], to [[go away#Verb|go away]]}}. Compare modern {{cog|cmn|死}}.

In kanji compounds, this would be considered as {{glink/ja|on'yomi}}; but on its own, this could be considered as either ''on'yomi'' or {{glink/ja|kun'yomi}}.

